---
import SubpageLayout from '../../../layouts/SubpageLayout.astro';
---

<SubpageLayout
  lang="en"
  title="EU Training"
  subtitle="Digital risk and European alternatives. A half-day or full-day session on location."
  seoDescription="EU Training: understand the risks of American platforms and discover European alternatives. Half-day or full-day session on location. By AI Heroes."
  accentColor="red"
  pillarBadge="Training"
  ctaLabel="Book a workshop"
  trustedBy={["Tweede Kamer", "Hanze", "Envalior"]}
>
  <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
    <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-serif text-brand-dark mb-6">Digital risk and European alternatives</h2>

    <div class="bg-red-950 text-white p-6 md:p-8 mb-8 border-l-4 border-brand-red not-prose">
      <p class="text-sm font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-brand-red mb-3">Why now</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-stone-200 mb-2">From <strong class="text-white">February 2025</strong>, the EU AI Act requires organisations to demonstrate AI literacy (Article 4). From <strong class="text-white">August 2025</strong>, the general provisions take effect. Meanwhile, the CLOUD Act gives the US access to data at American providers, regardless of server location.</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-stone-200">Organisations that don't act now risk compliance fines, data exposure to foreign jurisdictions and strategic dependency.</p>
    </div>

    <p class="text-stone-600 leading-relaxed mb-8">Most organisations know that something is shifting. American tech platforms are under increasing scrutiny, European regulation is tightening, and the question of digital sovereignty is moving from policy papers to boardrooms. But what does this actually mean for your organisation? What are the real risks, and what can you realistically do about them?</p>

    <div class="bg-stone-50 p-6 md:p-8 mb-8 border-l-4 border-brand-red not-prose">
      <h3 class="text-xl font-serif text-brand-dark mb-3">What the session covers</h3>
      <ol class="space-y-3 text-stone-600 list-decimal ml-5">
        <li><strong>The risks of American platforms:</strong> CLOUD Act, jurisdiction issues, and what happens when a foreign government can legally access your data.</li>
        <li><strong>The current landscape:</strong> actual tools your organisation uses, where your data flows, and where you are exposed.</li>
        <li><strong>European alternatives:</strong> what is genuinely good enough to replace current tools, and what is not ready yet.</li>
        <li><strong>The regulatory context:</strong> AI Act, NIS2, GDPR deadlines, and what non-compliance actually costs.</li>
      </ol>
    </div>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-serif text-brand-dark mb-4">Who it is for</h3>
    <p class="text-stone-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">Directors, IT leads and legal/compliance professionals at organisations with 10 to 150 staff. The session is designed for people who make or influence technology decisions, beyond just the IT department.</p>
    <p class="text-stone-600 leading-relaxed mb-8">We also offer a condensed 90-minute board-level session for management teams who need the essentials without the full deep dive.</p>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-serif text-brand-dark mb-4">Annual update</h3>
    <p class="text-stone-600 leading-relaxed mb-8">Regulation and technology change fast. We offer a light yearly update session to keep your team current on new developments, revised legislation and emerging European alternatives.</p>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 mb-8 not-prose">
      <div class="text-center p-6 bg-white border border-stone-200"><div class="text-3xl font-serif text-brand-red mb-2">½ - 1 day</div><div class="text-sm text-stone-500 uppercase tracking-wider">Session length</div></div>
      <div class="text-center p-6 bg-white border border-stone-200"><div class="text-3xl font-serif text-brand-red mb-2">10-150</div><div class="text-sm text-stone-500 uppercase tracking-wider">Employees</div></div>
      <div class="text-center p-6 bg-white border border-stone-200"><div class="text-3xl font-serif text-brand-red mb-2">On location</div><div class="text-sm text-stone-500 uppercase tracking-wider">Or online</div></div>
    </div>

    <div class="dark-box-content bg-brand-dark p-8 border-l-4 border-brand-blue my-8 not-prose">
      <h3>Next step</h3>
      <p>After the training, many organisations want to go deeper. Track B gives you a full <a href="/en/services/eu-consultancy" class="text-white underline underline-offset-2 hover:text-white/80">organisation scan and migration roadmap</a>. Track C helps you <a href="/en/services/eu-development" class="text-white underline underline-offset-2 hover:text-white/80">move to European AI tools</a>.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</SubpageLayout>
